<h2>About the Zone</h2>

<p class='info'>Updated August 2003 | Fredrik Lundh</p>
				
<h3 id='author'>About Me</h3>

<p>Fredrik Lundh.  I do Python stuff.
<a href="frank-willison-award.htm">Award-winning stuff</a>, at times.</p>

<h3 id='content'>About the Content</h3>

<p>Stuff.</p>

<h3 id='technology'>About the Technology</h3>

<p>The <b>zone.effbot.org</b> subsite is powered by a couple of very
simple Python scripts.  The main script allows me to create and edit
plain text files in a standard browser text area.  Every time I save
the text file, a simple renderer merges the text file with a predefined
template, pushes the result through <a href="http://www.w3.org/People/Raggett/tidy/">HTML Tidy</a>,
and writes the result to disk as a static HTML file.</p>

<p>Other scripts are used to look for broken links, download new and
updated pages and store them in a <s><a href="http://www.perforce.com">Perforce</a></s> <a href="subversion.htm">Subversion</a> repository, combine them into
<a href="http://online.effbot.org">a blog page</a>, etc.</p>

<p>I don't plan to release the scripts at this time.  If you need something
similar, I suggest using a real <a href="http://www.onlamp.com/pub/a/python/2000/11/29/pythonnews.html">Wiki</a>, such as <a href="http://moin.sourceforge.net/" title="don't let the fact that I couldn't figure out how to install it keep you from trying ;-)">MoinMoin</a>.</p>

<h3 id='cookies'>About our Cookies</h3>

<p>There are no cookies.</p>

<a href="http://effbot.org/rpc/fatherpoikilotherma.cgi"><div style="height: 0px; width: 0px;">&nbsp;</div></a>
